{"questionId":"7494","questionHtml":"<p>Two point charges <em>Q</em><sub>1</sub> and <em>Q</em><sub>2</sub> are one metre apart. The graph shows the variation of&nbsp;electric potential <em>V</em> with distance <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;from <em>Q</em><sub>1</sub>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/6d108f724c37dcbe1da58b54cb323bec0fc59e88.png\"></p>\n<p>What is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{Q_1}}}{{{Q_2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>Q</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>Q</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{16}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>16</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{{4}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; &nbsp;4</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;16</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7494","referenceCode":"18N.1.HL.TZ0.30","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two point charges Q1 and Q2 are one metre apart. The graph shows the variation of electric potential V with distance x from Q1. What is Q 1 Q 2 ? A. 1 16 B. 1 4 C. 4 D. 16","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"30","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: F